{
  "title": "O The Deep, Deep Love of Jesus",
  "key": "f minor",
  "key_root": "F",
  "mode": "minor",
  "meter": "8/4",
  "bpm": 100,
  "words": "S. Trevor Francis, 1875",
  "music": "or &#39;Ton-Y-Botel&#39; Thomas J. Williams, 1890",
  "tune": "Ebenezer",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "O the deep, deep love of Jesus, vast, unmeasured, boundless, free! Rolling as a mighty ocean in its fullness over me! Underneath me, all around me, is the current of Thy love Leading onward, leading homeward to Thy glorious rest above!",
    "v2": "O the deep, deep love of Jesus, spread His praise from shore to shore! How He loveth, ever loveth, changeth never, nevermore! How He watches o&#39;er His loved ones, died to call them all His own; How for them He intercedeth, watcheth o&#39;er them from the throne!",
    "v3": "O the deep, deep love of Jesus, love of every love the best! &#39;Tis an ocean full of blessing, &#39;tis a haven giving rest! O the deep, deep love of Jesus, &#39;tis a heav&#39;n of heav&#39;ns to me; And it lifts me up to glory, for it lifts me up to Thee!"
  },
